#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:442
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with Plain Zypper"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:444
#, no-c-format
msgid "If your system is not registered because you do not have access to the Internet or a registration server, migrating to a new service pack is not possible with &yast; Migration or <command>zypper migration</command> . In this case you can still migrate to a new service pack with plain Zypper and some manual interactions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:453
#, no-c-format
msgid "For Unregistered Systems Only"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:454
#, no-c-format
msgid "This migration path to a new service pack is <emphasis>only</emphasis> supported for unregistered systems that do not have access to the Internet or a registration server. This may, for example, be the case for machines in a specially protected network. In case you have a registered system, use &yast; or Zypper migration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:464
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installation Sources"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:465
#, no-c-format
msgid "This migration path requires you to provide the installation sources for the new service pack in a place that can be accessed by the machine you are going to migrate. This can for example be achieved by setting up an &rmt; server or an SLP server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:471
#, no-c-format
msgid "It is also required that the system has access to an up-to-date update repository for the installed product version."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:479
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you are logged in to a graphical session running on the machine you are going to migrate, log out of that session and switch to a text console. Running the update from within a graphical session is not recommended. Note that this does not apply when being logged in from a remote machine (unless you are running a VNC session with X)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:488
#, no-c-format
msgid "Update the package management tools with the old &sle; repositories:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:491
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper</command> patch --updatestack-only"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:494
#, no-c-format
msgid "Get a list of packages that currently do not have a repository assigned to them (orphaned packages). These packages will not be migrated and there is no guarantee that they will work after the migration (because other packages they rely on may have changed in a way they are no longer compatible). To get the list, run"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:502
#, no-c-format
msgid "Carefully review the list and remove all orphaned packages that are no longer needed. Make a note of all remaining orphaned packages, you will need it later for comparison."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:509
#, no-c-format
msgid "Get a list of all repositories that the system is currently subscribed to by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:513
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper repos -u"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:514
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the following you need to rewrite the repository URLs so they point to the respective repositories for the new service pack ( <literal>SLE-15</literal> needs to be replaced with <literal>SLE-15-SP1</literal> . If the URL for a repository looks like this:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:521
#, no-c-format
msgid "http://rmt.&exampledomain;/repo/SUSE/Products/SLE-15-Product-SLES/x86_64/product/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:522
#, no-c-format
msgid "it needs to be changed to"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:525
#, no-c-format
msgid "http://rmt.&exampledomain;/repo/SUSE/Products/SLE-15-SP1-Product-SLES/x86_64/product/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:526
#, no-c-format
msgid "This needs to be done with all repositories that are enabled. You may want to consider also doing this for repositories that are currently disabled, to avoid having wrong installation sources in the system when activating them at a later point in time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:532
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change the repository URLs you have the following options:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:537
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using <menuchoice> <guimenu>&yast;</guimenu> <guimenu>Software</guimenu> <guimenu>Software Repositories</guimenu></menuchoice> . Select a repository and click <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> to make the required change. Repeat this for all repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:545
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using Zypper. Add a new repository and remove the corresponding old one afterwards:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:549
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper addrepo -f <replaceable>URL</replaceable> <replaceable>NAME</replaceable>-15-SP1\n"
      "&prompt.sudo;zypper removerepo  <replaceable>NAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:553
#, no-c-format
msgid "By editing repository configuration files in <filename>/etc/zypp/repos.d</filename> . Each repository is represented by one configuration file. Changing the value for the <literal>baseurl</literal> parameter is required in each file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:563
#, no-c-format
msgid "Review your changes by running <command>zypper repos -u</command> and update the repositories by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:568
#, no-c-format
msgid "In case updating a repository fails, double-check whether you entered the wrong URL. If the problem cannot be fixed, it is recommended to disable the failing repository."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:573
#, no-c-format
msgid "If all repositories are correctly configured, run"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:576
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper refresh -f -s"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:577
#, no-c-format
msgid "again, to make sure <emphasis>all</emphasis> repositories are up-to-date."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:582
#, no-c-format
msgid "Before starting the migration it is recommended do a test run first:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:585
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper dup -D --no-allow-vendor-change --no-recommends"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:586
#, no-c-format
msgid "The parameter <option>-D</option> will perform a dry-run, that simulates the migration without actually changing the system. In case problems occur, fix them before proceeding. In case the test run succeeds, perform the real migration by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:592
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper dup --no-allow-vendor-change --no-recommends"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:593
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-no-allow-vendor-change</option> ensures that third-party RPMs will not overwrite RPMs from the base system. The option <option>--no-recommends</option> ensures that packages deselected during initial installation will not be added again."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:601
#, no-c-format
msgid "When the migration has finished and the system has booted into the new service pack version, run the check for orphaned packages again:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:605
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper packages --orphaned"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:606
#, no-c-format
msgid "Compare the new list with the one you generated before starting the migration. In case new packages appear in the list, it may be because they were moved to a different module in the new service pack. In case you did not have that module in the previous installation, the package did not get updated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:613
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can check to which module a package belongs at <link xlink:href=\"https://scc.suse.com/packages\"/> . Add the missing modules using <command>zypper addrepo</command> or the &yast; Software Repositories module, and update the orphaned packages afterwards by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:620
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper install --no-recommends <replaceable>LIST OF PACKAGES</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:623
#, no-c-format
msgid "You have successfully migrated to a new service pack!"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:631
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rolling Back a Service Pack"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:633
#, no-c-format
msgid "If a service pack does not work for you, &sle; supports reverting the system to the state before the service pack migration was started. Prerequisite is a Btrfs root partition with snapshots enabled (this has been the default since &slsa;&nbsp;12). See <xref linkend=\"cha-snapper\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:641
#, no-c-format
msgid "Get a list of all Snapper snapshots:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:644
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;snapper list"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:645
#, no-c-format
msgid "Review the output to locate the snapshot that was created immediately before the service pack migration was started. The column <guimenu>Description</guimenu> contains a corresponding statement and the snapshot is marked as <literal>important</literal> in the column <guimenu>Userdata</guimenu> . Memorize the snapshot number from the column <guimenu>#</guimenu> and its date from the column <guimenu>Date</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:656
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reboot the system. From the boot menu, select <guimenu>Start boot loader from a read-only snapshot</guimenu> and then choose the snapshot with the date and number you memorized in the previous step. A second boot menu (the one from the snapshot) is loaded. Select the entry starting with &slsa;&nbsp;&productnumber; and boot it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:665
#, no-c-format
msgid "The system boots into the previous state with the system partition mounted read-only. Log in as &rootuser; and check whether you have chosen the correct snapshot. Also make sure everything works as expected. Note that since the root file system is mounted read-only, restrictions in functionality may apply."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:672
#, no-c-format
msgid "In case of problems or if you have booted the wrong snapshot, reboot and choose a different snapshot to boot from&mdash;up to this point no permanent changes have been made. If the snapshot is correct and works as expected, make the change permanent by running the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:678
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;snapper rollback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:679
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reboot afterward. On the boot screen, choose the default boot entry to reboot into the reinstated system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:685
#, no-c-format
msgid "Check if the repository configuration has been properly reset. Furthermore, check if all products are properly registered. If either one is not the case, updating the system at a later point in time may no longer work, or the system may be updated using the wrong package repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:692
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make sure the system can access the Internet before starting this procedure."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:698
#, no-c-format
msgid "Refresh services and repositories by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:701
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper ref -fs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:704
#, no-c-format
msgid "Get a list of active repositories by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:707
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper lr"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:708
#, no-c-format
msgid "Carefully check the output of this command. No services and repositories that were added for the update should be listed. For example, if you are rolling back from &slsa;15 SP1 to &slsa;15, the list must contain the <literal>SLES15</literal> repositories, and not the <literal>SLES15-SP1</literal> repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:715
#, no-c-format
msgid "If wrong repositories are listed, delete them and, if necessary, replace them with the versions matching your product or service pack version. For a list of repositories for the supported migration paths refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-upgrade-background-modules\"/> . (Note that manual intervention should not be necessary, as the repositories should be updated automatically, but it is a best practice to verify and make any necessary corrections.)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:725
#, no-c-format
msgid "Last, check the registration status for all products installed by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:729
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;SUSEConnect --status"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:730
#, no-c-format
msgid "All products should be reported as being <literal>Registered</literal> . If this is not the case, repair the registration by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:735
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;SUSEConnect --rollback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:740
#, no-c-format
msgid "Now you have successfully reverted the system to the state that was captured immediately before the service pack migration was started."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:747
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with &susemgr;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:749
#, no-c-format
msgid "&susemgr; is a server solution for providing updates, patches, and security fixes for &sle; clients. It comes with a set of tools and a Web-based user interface for management tasks. See <link xlink:href=\"https://www.suse.com/products/suse-manager/\"/> for more information about &susemgr;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:757
#, no-c-format
msgid "SP Migration allows migrating from one Service Pack (SP) to another within one major version (for example, from &slsa;&nbsp;15&nbsp;GA to &slsa;&nbsp;15&nbsp;SP1)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:767
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading from &opensuse; Leap to &productname;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:768
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can upgrade an &opensuse; installation online to &productname;. The procedure is analogous to <xref linkend=\"sec-upgrade-online-zypper\"/> , but some additional steps are required. Before executing this procedure on a production system, we recommend to first run it on a test system that replicates your production setup."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:775
#, no-c-format
msgid "To see for which &opensuse; Leap versions a migration is supported, read <xref linkend=\"sec-upgrade-paths-supported\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:780
#, no-c-format
msgid "Not All &opensuse; Packages Can Be Migrated"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:781
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &opensuse; repositories provide more packages than are available in the &productname; repositories. If you have any of these packages installed, they will no longer receive updates after the migration. These packages will be removed when following the procedure below."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:788
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make sure that all packages you need for operating your system are available in the &productname; repository. You can also check if the packages are available in the &suse; Package Hub repository. For details, see <xref linkend=\"sec-add-ons-package-hub\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:795
#, no-c-format
msgid "To migrate from &opensuse; Leap, execute the following procedure:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:800
#, no-c-format
msgid "Switch to a TTY, for example by pressing <keycombo><keycap>Ctrl</keycap> <keycap>Alt</keycap><keycap>F1</keycap></keycombo> . Then log in as &rootuser;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:807
#, no-c-format
msgid "Install <package>SUSEConnect</package> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:808
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>zypper in SUSEConnect</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:819
#, no-c-format
msgid "Register at SCC to get the &productname; repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:820
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>SUSEConnect -r <replaceable>REGISTRATION_CODE</replaceable> -p SLES/15.1/x86_64</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:823
#, no-c-format
msgid "List and disable all &opensuse; repositories on your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:826
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>zypper lr</command>\n"
      "&prompt.root;<command>zypper mr -d <replaceable>REPO_IDS</replaceable></command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:828
#, no-c-format
msgid "Replace <replaceable>REPO_IDS</replaceable> with a space character separated list of all enabled &opensuse; repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:834
#, no-c-format
msgid "Now add the modules you need for your installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:837
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>SUSEConnect --list-extensions</command>\n"
      "[...]\n"
      "&prompt.root;<command>SUSEConnect -p sle-module-basesystem/15.1/x86_64</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:840
#, no-c-format
msgid "To have replacements for most Leap packages, we recommend to enable the Basesystem, Desktop Applications, Server Applications and Legacy modules. Additionally, we recommend to enable the &suse; Package Hub."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:848
#, no-c-format
msgid "Migrate installed packages to the &productname; repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:851
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>zypper dup --force-resolution</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:854
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remove orphaned packages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:855
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>zypper rm $(zypper --no-refresh packages --orphaned | gawk '{print $5}' | tail -n +5)</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:858
#, no-c-format
msgid "Finally, reboot the system."
msgstr ""

